other_tests.findings: Focal fat seen in hepatic segment 4. No intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. Gallbladder is normal with no sludge or stone. Pancreas is homogeneous in signal with no focal lesion or pancreatic ductal dilatation. Normal spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, and gastrointestinal tract. No lymphadenopathy or vascular issues. A 1.0 cm T2 hyperintense heterogeneously enhancing lesion with 0.7 cm collection in the anterior abdominal wall suggestive of resolving infectious/collection.
